WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:29.861 --> 00:00:34.031
(Azure Spring)

00:00:34.032 --> 00:00:36.433
(All characters, places, events, etc.. depicted are fictional.)

00:00:36.434 --> 00:00:38.970
(Children and animals were filmed under strict guidelines.)

00:00:46.344 --> 00:00:47.913
Where did they go this time?

00:01:06.231 --> 00:01:07.432
Unbelievable.

00:01:08.733 --> 00:01:10.168
Seo An Na, you...

00:01:22.814 --> 00:01:28.820
(Episode 3: The Timing)

00:01:32.757 --> 00:01:35.493
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

00:01:44.436 --> 00:01:46.716
Doing this prevents your goggles from fogging underwater.

00:01:49.007 --> 00:01:50.976
Like anti-fog coating?

00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:54.179
The sea works around its own clock.

00:01:55.614 --> 00:01:57.349
High tide, low tide, and the tidal cycle.

00:01:58.116 --> 00:01:59.217
I know that much.

00:01:59.451 --> 00:02:02.554
You knew that, yet you went in during the most dangerous time?

00:02:04.856 --> 00:02:05.891
I did?

00:02:07.526 --> 00:02:08.860
You got swept away instantly...

00:02:09.528 --> 00:02:10.862
by the strong current.

00:02:19.871 --> 00:02:21.805
The time when the current is weakest...

00:02:21.806 --> 00:02:24.166
between the low and the high tide is called the slack tide.

00:02:25.210 --> 00:02:26.844
It is the only time, occurring twice a day,

00:02:26.845 --> 00:02:29.181
when the sea allows free divers to harvest seafood.

00:02:30.682 --> 00:02:32.551
So when is that?

00:02:34.386 --> 00:02:35.487
Right now.

00:02:40.892 --> 00:02:42.928
You're right. I guess...

00:02:43.495 --> 00:02:45.197
it seems rather peaceful.

00:02:46.264 --> 00:02:47.432
Let's go in.

00:02:49.234 --> 00:02:51.670
The slack tide lasts only three hours at most.

00:02:59.811 --> 00:03:00.979
Wait up!

00:03:04.149 --> 00:03:05.250
Hey, wait up!

00:03:05.990 --> 00:03:07.292
I said, wait for me!

00:03:37.782 --> 00:03:39.150
Stand straight. You're heavy.

00:03:43.288 --> 00:03:44.389
I'm not that...

00:03:46.925 --> 00:03:49.461
Hey! You two jerks!

00:03:53.498 --> 00:03:54.533
Baek Su Jeong?

00:03:55.901 --> 00:03:58.470
Seo An Na, I'm the idiot...

00:03:59.738 --> 00:04:01.106
for trusting you.

00:04:02.674 --> 00:04:04.341
You wench!

00:04:04.342 --> 00:04:06.211
Hey, you're going to fall!

00:04:09.748 --> 00:04:11.683
Stop pretending like you're nice.

00:04:12.083 --> 00:04:13.951
What? What are you talking about?

00:04:13.952 --> 00:04:16.153
You said you weren't into Duk Hyun!

00:04:16.154 --> 00:04:18.656
How can you do this to me?

00:04:18.657 --> 00:04:20.424
I'm not!

00:04:20.425 --> 00:04:22.661
You said you didn't get what was sexy about him.

00:04:22.861 --> 00:04:25.262
What? "Sexy"? You call that guy sexy?

00:04:25.263 --> 00:04:26.531
You!

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:29.501
Hey!

00:04:30.135 --> 00:04:31.169
You two...

00:04:40.745 --> 00:04:43.148
Duk Hyun, do me first.

00:04:43.682 --> 00:04:45.550
I'm more badly hurt.

00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:50.255
Please settle this on your own.

00:04:52.123 --> 00:04:53.458
Where are you going?

00:04:53.792 --> 00:04:55.459
I have an ouchie right here.

00:04:55.460 --> 00:04:57.394
You need to put some medicine on me.

00:04:57.395 --> 00:04:58.896
Duk Hyun!

00:04:58.897 --> 00:05:01.299
Hey, I got you.

00:05:03.235 --> 00:05:04.336
Come closer.

00:05:07.939 --> 00:05:09.374
Stay still.

00:05:09.941 --> 00:05:10.942
Jeez.

00:05:11.476 --> 00:05:14.246
Even if you do this, I still won't let it slide.

00:05:15.547 --> 00:05:18.016
It's nothing like what you're imagining.

00:05:18.450 --> 00:05:19.584
It so is.

00:05:19.918 --> 00:05:22.921
You two harvest seafood together, eat together,

00:05:23.154 --> 00:05:24.555
work out together,

00:05:24.556 --> 00:05:27.791
touch each other, and feel each other up!

00:05:27.792 --> 00:05:28.793
Hey!

00:05:28.927 --> 00:05:30.828
I like men who aren't tanned...

00:05:30.829 --> 00:05:32.097
and are sweet.

00:05:32.664 --> 00:05:33.899
Exactly.

00:05:34.332 --> 00:05:38.303
Duk Hyun has such a sweet and handsome face!

00:05:39.738 --> 00:05:41.239
Su Jeong, please.

00:05:44.342 --> 00:05:46.845
You and I aren't besties anymore.

00:05:47.612 --> 00:05:49.714
This is war, you traitor.

00:05:50.215 --> 00:05:53.451
Don't ever act friendly and call me Su Jeong without my surname,

00:05:54.085 --> 00:05:56.021
Seo An Na.

00:06:01.159 --> 00:06:03.061
We weren't best friends to start with.

00:06:05.030 --> 00:06:06.364
That was a decade ago.

00:06:29.654 --> 00:06:30.934
Aren't you going out to harvest?

00:06:31.456 --> 00:06:33.190
I already told you.

00:06:33.191 --> 00:06:35.427
The slack tide only lasts three hours at most.

00:06:37.395 --> 00:06:38.396
Also,

00:06:39.197 --> 00:06:41.466
you'd better not touch the water for a while.

00:06:45.437 --> 00:06:46.605
You know what?

00:06:47.539 --> 00:06:48.907
You're rude,

00:06:49.708 --> 00:06:51.109
but you're also oddly sweet.

00:06:51.977 --> 00:06:52.978
Impossible.

00:06:58.416 --> 00:07:00.951
Even if you didn't get to harvest, wash the suit before drying it.

00:07:00.952 --> 00:07:03.112
Even a little bit of salt can easily corrode the suit.

00:07:04.623 --> 00:07:05.991
Yeah, yeah.

00:07:07.559 --> 00:07:08.927
I shouldn't have said anything.

00:07:09.895 --> 00:07:10.896
Also,

00:07:11.329 --> 00:07:13.009
clear the air between you and your friend.

00:07:14.699 --> 00:07:15.699
Why?

00:07:15.700 --> 00:07:17.334
Are you scared you'll be known around the island...

00:07:17.335 --> 00:07:18.937
as a player who's toying with two girls?

00:07:21.239 --> 00:07:23.519
Just like the sea, there's a right timing between people.

00:07:24.809 --> 00:07:26.129
If you miss it, you won't find...

00:07:27.712 --> 00:07:29.414
another chance for a very long time.

00:07:34.920 --> 00:07:36.288
I shouldn't have been so nosy.

00:07:44.029 --> 00:07:45.030
What was that?

00:07:46.097 --> 00:07:47.165
Trying to act all cool.

00:07:52.070 --> 00:07:54.939
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

00:07:54.940 --> 00:07:57.542
Well, I guess I had always pushed everything aside...

00:07:58.310 --> 00:07:59.744
except for swimming.

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:04.015
I told you to stop sending me food.

00:08:04.449 --> 00:08:06.051
I can't even finish these.

00:08:06.551 --> 00:08:08.653
I feed myself all right.

00:08:09.054 --> 00:08:10.789
Stop worrying about me.

00:08:12.324 --> 00:08:13.859
No, I said I'm fine!

00:08:15.727 --> 00:08:17.362
"I'm busy now, so maybe later."

00:08:21.333 --> 00:08:23.134
"I can always do it next time,"

00:08:23.869 --> 00:08:24.903
"so maybe later."

00:08:44.656 --> 00:08:47.592
You little brat. You didn't even touch these.

00:08:50.095 --> 00:08:51.630
Do you know how hurtful this is?

00:08:55.033 --> 00:08:56.701
I kept pushing everything back,

00:08:57.135 --> 00:08:58.170
and in the end,

00:08:59.137 --> 00:09:00.272
I ended up hurting her.

00:09:15.954 --> 00:09:17.155
I missed...

00:09:18.623 --> 00:09:19.658
the important timing.

00:09:20.792 --> 00:09:23.628
(Parang-ri Haenyeo Cho Mi Hyeon)

00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:29.367
How am I...

00:09:30.535 --> 00:09:32.270
supposed to clear the air between us?

00:10:12.143 --> 00:10:13.278
Are these red beans?

00:10:14.312 --> 00:10:15.981
Jeez, I have no idea.

00:10:17.048 --> 00:10:19.518
After all, this isn't the supermarket.

00:10:20.151 --> 00:10:21.271
I doubt there are red beans.

00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:23.622
Even if there were, it's not yet time.

00:10:27.425 --> 00:10:29.665
Red beans are sown in the summer and reaped in the fall.

00:10:32.664 --> 00:10:34.032
Thanks for the info.

00:10:40.172 --> 00:10:42.140
What? You said there weren't any.

00:10:42.474 --> 00:10:44.275
I just said it wasn't harvest season yet.

00:10:44.276 --> 00:10:45.343
These are from last year.

00:10:47.746 --> 00:10:48.880
Thanks.

00:11:34.392 --> 00:11:35.393
Hey.

00:11:36.328 --> 00:11:37.329
Hey!

00:11:39.030 --> 00:11:41.766
Why don't you help me, so that I don't miss the timing?

00:11:48.340 --> 00:11:49.908
Go. Come on.

00:11:55.213 --> 00:11:56.214
Open it.

00:12:04.523 --> 00:12:05.523
Come on.

00:12:05.524 --> 00:12:06.558
Stir it like this.

00:12:33.084 --> 00:12:34.653
Keep going.

00:13:08.453 --> 00:13:11.356
When you think about it, timing is everything.

00:13:19.865 --> 00:13:20.932
In harvesting seafood,

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:22.701
relationships,

00:13:23.935 --> 00:13:24.936
and making dough.

00:13:26.004 --> 00:13:27.539
It's all about timing.

00:13:57.369 --> 00:13:58.569
How long do I have to do this?

00:13:59.070 --> 00:14:00.338
Bring it over here.

00:15:06.738 --> 00:15:07.772
Look at this.

00:15:48.713 --> 00:15:50.148
A long wait and perfect timing...

00:15:50.916 --> 00:15:52.317
are required even when you make...

00:15:53.218 --> 00:15:54.953
these simple honey donuts.

00:15:56.188 --> 00:15:58.523
Everything comes down to timing.

00:16:05.230 --> 00:16:06.231
Try one.

00:16:22.781 --> 00:16:26.083
Come to Parang Elementary School. Immediately. Right now.

00:16:26.084 --> 00:16:27.586
(Seo An Na)

00:16:38.897 --> 00:16:40.098
Jeez, that girl.

00:16:40.465 --> 00:16:42.200
Why did she call me out all the way here?

00:16:57.482 --> 00:16:58.783
What the heck, Su Jeong?

00:16:59.150 --> 00:17:01.086
You called me here, yet you show up late.

00:17:02.387 --> 00:17:04.489
Here. Have it on your way to Seoul.

00:17:11.029 --> 00:17:12.597
Gosh, honey donuts?

00:17:13.098 --> 00:17:15.858
I got sick of these here. Are you telling me to eat it in Seoul, too?

00:17:16.735 --> 00:17:19.905
You didn't even tell me you were moving to Seoul,

00:17:20.939 --> 00:17:23.074
so I didn't have time to prepare a present.

00:17:32.117 --> 00:17:34.986
What is this? Do you think some donuts are enough to call it even?

00:17:35.720 --> 00:17:37.222
These aren't just some donuts.

00:17:37.856 --> 00:17:39.057
You once said...

00:17:39.558 --> 00:17:42.627
that honey donuts are a way of saying, "Have a safe trip."

00:17:49.334 --> 00:17:51.036
I told you to have them on your way there.

00:17:52.737 --> 00:17:55.407
It doesn't matter where you eat these.

00:17:55.640 --> 00:17:57.909
It does! My dad said...

00:17:58.476 --> 00:18:01.646
honey donuts are made with a lot of syrup, so they last long.

00:18:02.314 --> 00:18:04.582
That's why my mom always makes them...

00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:06.451
for my dad before he goes out to sea.

00:18:08.687 --> 00:18:10.407
It's her way of saying, "Have a safe trip."

00:18:25.003 --> 00:18:27.639
So these aren't just any honey donuts.

00:18:28.773 --> 00:18:29.875
They're my way of saying,

00:18:32.477 --> 00:18:33.545
"Thanks to you."

00:18:34.646 --> 00:18:37.148
"I had a great trip, Baek Su Jeong."

00:18:39.351 --> 00:18:41.019
Whatever, girl.

00:18:43.588 --> 00:18:45.657
Wait, are you crying?

00:18:47.926 --> 00:18:50.629
I'm not crying. I just got thirsty.

00:18:55.667 --> 00:18:57.569
Hey, did you just laugh at me?

00:18:57.802 --> 00:18:59.704
Yes, I did. So what?

00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:04.009
So? Do you like it?

00:19:04.609 --> 00:19:05.769
I've never made these before.

00:19:09.014 --> 00:19:10.115
These are really...

00:19:13.251 --> 00:19:14.252
delicious.

00:19:18.056 --> 00:19:20.258
Doing this won't make me give up on Duk Hyun for you.

00:19:20.525 --> 00:19:21.993
Don't you dare try to steal him.

00:19:23.061 --> 00:19:26.097
- Gosh, I'm not interested! - Aren't you lying?

00:19:28.466 --> 00:19:29.834
- What the heck? - It's raining.

00:19:29.835 --> 00:19:30.836
It's raining!

00:19:32.237 --> 00:19:34.639
The sky is so clear. Why is it suddenly raining?

00:19:35.207 --> 00:19:36.274
Run!

00:19:58.163 --> 00:20:00.264
A typhoon is coming. We can't go harvesting for a while.

00:20:00.265 --> 00:20:01.266
What?

00:20:04.302 --> 00:20:05.702
What are you doing? Give me a hand.

00:20:09.274 --> 00:20:11.710
There's a time for everything.

00:20:14.579 --> 00:20:17.648
A typhoon is moving rapidly northward.

00:20:17.649 --> 00:20:21.185
Heavy rain is expected across the country for the time being,

00:20:21.186 --> 00:20:24.655
with localized downpours exceeding 80mm per hour...

00:20:24.656 --> 00:20:27.825
along the southern coast, raising concerns about possible damage.

00:20:27.826 --> 00:20:31.963
The weather is expected to be at its worst from tonight through dawn.

00:20:33.732 --> 00:20:34.900
- Darn it. - My gosh!

00:20:36.468 --> 00:20:37.536
Come on!

00:20:39.437 --> 00:20:41.038
What are you doing? Stick it on!

00:20:41.039 --> 00:20:42.374
Give me a moment, will you?

00:20:44.276 --> 00:20:45.577
Hold this, please!

00:21:01.359 --> 00:21:02.894
While you wait for the right timing,

00:21:03.295 --> 00:21:05.030
you may face a huge ordeal...

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:06.998
and may even fall apart.

00:21:16.675 --> 00:21:18.176
But even the fiercest storms...

00:21:19.144 --> 00:21:20.345
eventually pass.

00:21:37.329 --> 00:21:38.396
Shall we go today?

00:21:42.767 --> 00:21:43.768
To harvest seafood.

00:22:04.356 --> 00:22:07.292
When the storm passes and the impurities are gone,

00:22:11.830 --> 00:22:13.932
the sea is ready to give new life.

00:22:19.471 --> 00:22:22.440
Just like that, the timing comes.

00:22:27.479 --> 00:22:28.480
Let's go.

00:22:42.294 --> 00:22:43.595
Wait!

00:22:46.498 --> 00:22:47.899
No one should go out to dive...

00:22:50.468 --> 00:22:51.536
on an empty stomach.

00:22:53.438 --> 00:22:55.040
I do it on an empty stomach.

00:22:56.060 --> 00:22:58.162
Oh, my.

00:22:58.502 --> 00:23:02.106
Then you can eat your food during lunch.

00:23:03.181 --> 00:23:05.684
What about me? I can eat now.

00:23:06.777 --> 00:23:08.078
Yours?

00:23:08.900 --> 00:23:09.901
I don't have any.

00:23:15.026 --> 00:23:16.094
Good luck.

00:23:47.692 --> 00:23:48.860
Let's dive in here.

00:23:52.464 --> 00:23:53.765
This is different from swimming.

00:23:54.633 --> 00:23:56.993
You need to hold your breath in, instead of letting it out.

00:23:58.837 --> 00:24:00.172
Holding my breath in?

00:24:02.574 --> 00:24:03.808
Then I'll see you down below.

00:25:11.243 --> 00:25:13.078
I can't tell anything apart.

00:25:19.818 --> 00:25:21.286
Where did you find that?

00:25:22.287 --> 00:25:24.122
Did you buy that while I wasn't looking?

00:25:24.656 --> 00:25:26.258
Did you forget everything I told you?

00:25:26.591 --> 00:25:28.193
I remember everything!

00:25:28.527 --> 00:25:29.767
But it's easier said than done.

00:25:31.396 --> 00:25:32.464
Put your goggles on.

00:25:35.534 --> 00:25:36.568
And then,

00:25:37.469 --> 00:25:39.371
- give me your hand. - What?

00:25:42.140 --> 00:25:44.376
- Now, breathe in. - Darn it.

00:26:25.584 --> 00:26:27.586
When you're underwater, it'll look like this.

00:26:28.987 --> 00:26:30.789
This looks like a rock.

00:26:33.325 --> 00:26:34.359
Do you see those?

00:26:36.628 --> 00:26:38.630
I see. Are those respiratory pores?

00:26:41.733 --> 00:26:43.502
Rocks don't have these holes.

00:26:44.469 --> 00:26:46.605
When you're underwater, take your time...

00:26:47.105 --> 00:26:48.740
to examine the rocks.

00:26:49.307 --> 00:26:50.976
Then you'll feel the abalones breathing.

00:27:52.571 --> 00:27:55.173
I found one! I caught it!

00:27:55.974 --> 00:27:58.376
What? What did you catch?

00:27:59.244 --> 00:28:00.245
An abalone!

00:28:03.515 --> 00:28:06.084
No way. An abalone?

00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:08.587
That's my Parang-ri Mermaid!

00:28:08.720 --> 00:28:10.989
Nice job, An Na!

00:28:15.160 --> 00:28:16.194
Look!

00:28:22.901 --> 00:28:25.303
Don't get too excited or ambitious after catching one.

00:28:25.470 --> 00:28:26.905
Do as much as your breath allows.

00:28:27.405 --> 00:28:28.607
Stop nagging.

00:28:30.442 --> 00:28:33.245
I've been waiting for this day for a long time.

00:28:33.778 --> 00:28:34.779
Have some faith in me.

00:28:35.947 --> 00:28:37.048
See you down there.

00:30:18.517 --> 00:30:20.237
If I continue to wait for the right timing,

00:30:21.653 --> 00:30:22.654
will my dream...

00:30:24.356 --> 00:30:25.857
ever see the light of day again...

00:30:27.559 --> 00:30:28.627
someday?

00:30:46.444 --> 00:30:47.679
Are you that happy?

00:30:48.613 --> 00:30:50.482
Yes, and I owe it to you.

00:30:53.118 --> 00:30:54.186
I feel great.

00:30:55.554 --> 00:30:57.856
I take back what I said last time.

00:31:00.492 --> 00:31:01.893
That you were rude...

00:31:02.761 --> 00:31:04.296
but oddly sweet.

00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:06.064
Then what?

00:31:07.032 --> 00:31:10.101
You aren't rude, but you aren't sweet, either.

00:31:12.437 --> 00:31:14.139
Isn't that worse?

00:31:14.940 --> 00:31:16.074
Instead,

00:31:16.842 --> 00:31:19.010
you remind me of the sea.

00:31:23.215 --> 00:31:25.684
On the surface, you surge with waves and push people away.

00:31:26.451 --> 00:31:28.186
But you're deep and peaceful on the inside.

00:31:30.121 --> 00:31:33.291
Although I haven't known you for long,

00:31:34.693 --> 00:31:36.161
I feel like I can trust you.

00:31:43.268 --> 00:31:44.769
You're a bad judge of character.

00:31:45.804 --> 00:31:47.706
Jeez, I know you liked it.

00:31:48.473 --> 00:31:51.176
Anyway, thank you...

00:31:55.814 --> 00:31:58.517
for teaching me how to harvest seafood.

00:32:38.356 --> 00:32:40.425
Hey. You.

00:32:44.029 --> 00:32:46.698
I heard this guy lives here. Is that right?

00:32:48.333 --> 00:32:49.367
Who's that?

00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:54.372
Hey, yes. Yoon Duk Hyun!

00:32:55.140 --> 00:32:57.308
That's Yoon Duk Hyun!

00:32:57.309 --> 00:33:00.345
He lives over there in that house with a red roof.

00:33:03.215 --> 00:33:05.851
By the way, why are you...

00:33:06.685 --> 00:33:08.086
looking for him?

00:33:12.724 --> 00:33:13.825
May I ask why?

00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:15.660
Why?

00:33:18.129 --> 00:33:19.531
Is he someone I shouldn't look for?

00:33:21.466 --> 00:33:24.169
No, it's not that.

00:33:28.974 --> 00:33:32.243
It's because he owes me something.

00:33:32.244 --> 00:33:33.278
